##What is Abstraction
Abstraction means hiding the implementation details and showing only the functionality to the user.

It helps to reduce complexity and increase security.

Example: Car → Innova / Maruthi
abstract class Car {

abstract void start();

abstract void stop();
}

class Innova extends Car {

void start(){
    System.out.println("Innova starts with push button");
}

void stop(){
    System.out.println("Innova stops smoothly");
}
}

class Maruthi extends Car {

void start(){
    System.out.println("Maruthi starts with key");
}

void stop(){
    System.out.println("Maruthi stops normally");
}
}

public class Main {

public static void main(String[] args) {

    Car c1 = new Innova();
    c1.start();
    c1.stop();

    Car c2 = new Maruthi();
    c2.start();
    c2.stop();

}
}

Output
Innova starts with push button
Innova stops smoothly
Maruthi starts with key
Maruthi stops normally
